705435f-a.text:
Liberty Avenue, at the S.E. corner of New Jersey Avenue, showing the St. Johannes Evangeliach-Lutheriache Kirche. This edifice was later razed and a brick church erected on the east side of New Jersey Avenue, about 115 feet to the south of Liberty Avenue.

About 1890
Eugene L. Arabrueter Collection
